<br>
I was recently looking through my collection of old AD&amp;D, Middle Earth, GURPs, and Rolemaster stuff.....and I picked up some Forgotten Realms material and started looking through it when I realized that I could of put out a lot better quality material. It was kinda that &quot;Hey I could do better than this&quot;. Anyways I have been kind of tinkering around with a fantasy plot and characters in my mind for the past month or two and I'm getting the feeling I should put pen to paper. <br>
<br>
I have played fantasy role playing games since early junior high through my time in tne military and college. I guess if I had to assess myself in regards to this industry it would be my creativity and ability to put together &quot;high fantasy&quot; orientated adventures, plots, characters, settings, etc. I'm a little nervous about my writing ability though...so I was more leaning towards designing a fantasy setting with supplemental materials such as setting information and adventures rather than writing a novel. However the format the original Conan books were written in suits me; a collection of short stories.<br>
<br>
I already have a trio of heros created: an outcast dwarf warrior, a half elf ranger with minor wizard and bardic skills such as a small arsenal of spells and a respectable amount of lore, and a great northman (barbarian) who is both skilled warrior and talented thief. The story is set in a world I created and it deals with the heros seeking out and destroying the lost bones of the greatest dragon ever to live. See, a highly secretive and evil cabal of wizards (necromancers) are seeking these bones to bring the dragon back in undead form and of course wreack havoc, and pillage =P The wizards (necromancers) are part of an ancient cabal that has long ago become undead...but they still seek to gain power and conquer the known world. The dragon bones are seperated and spread throughout the land in dungeons, vaults of high kings, another plane of existance, etc etc.<br>
<br>
Well anyway thats what I have so far and I am seeking to take it further ...I already have a lot of old parchment sheets 3'x3' to make maps and etc. So if anyone has any experience on doingh this sort of thing let me know....also PLEASE tell me if my idea has already been done, is taken, is pretty common, etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
BTW the characters are pretty unique except I do admit my fondness for Fafhrd (Fafhrd and the Grey Mouser; Fritz Leiber) kind of inspired the idea for my northman character....but what the heck?<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
